    In text, lexical cohesion is the result of chains of related words that contribute to the continuity of lexical meaning.
    These lexical chains are a direct result of units of text being &amp;quot;about the same thing,&amp;quot; and finding text structure involves finding units of text that are about the same thing.
    Hence, computing the chains is useful, since they will 